  "response": "Certainly! Here are some sentences using \"though\" in different contexts:\n\n1. **As a conjunction (similar to \"although\")**:\n   - Though it was raining, we decided to go for a walk.\n   - She agreed to help, though she was very busy.\n\n2. **At the end of a sentence (to add contrast or soften a statement)**:\n   - I don\u2019t usually like spicy food. This dish is really good, though.\n   - The movie was a bit long. I enjoyed it, though.\n\n3. **In the middle of a sentence (to introduce a contrast)**:\n   - He\u2019s very young, though he\u2019s incredibly talented.\n   - The hike was tough, though the view at the top made it worth it.\n\nLet me know if you'd like more examples!",
